#### MODULES ####

# The imjournal module bellow is now used as a message source instead of imuxsock.[m
$ModLoad imuxsock [34m# provides support for local system logging (e.g. via logger command)[m
$ModLoad imjournal [34m# provides access to the systemd journal
#$ModLoad imklog # reads kernel messages (the same are read from journald)
#$ModLoad immark  # provides --MARK-- message capability

# Provides UDP syslog reception

#$UDPServerRun 514

$ActionFileDefaultTemplate RSYSLOG_TraditionalFileFormat

[34m# File syncing capability is disabled by default. This feature is usually not required,
# not useful and an extreme performance hit
#$ActionFileEnableSync on

# Include all config files in /etc/rsyslog.d/[m
$IncludeConfig /etc/rsyslog.d/*.conf

[34m# Turn off message reception via local log socket;
# local messages are retrieved through imjournal now.[m
$OmitLocalLogging on

[34m# File to store the position in the journal[m

# For more information see /usr/share/doc/rsyslog-*/rsyslog_conf.html
# If you experience problems, see http://www.rsyslog.com/doc/troubleshoot.html

#### MODULES ####

# The imjournal module bellow is now used as a message source instead of imuxsock.[m
$ModLoad imuxsock [34m# provides support for local system logging (e.g. via logger command)[m
$ModLoad imjournal [34m# provides access to the systemd journal
#$ModLoad imklog # reads kernel messages (the same are read from journald)
#$ModLoad immark  # provides --MARK-- message capability

# Provides UDP syslog reception[m
$ModLoad imudp
$UDPServerRun 514

[34m# Provides TCP syslog reception[m
$ModLoad imtcp
$InputTCPServerRun 514


[34m#### GLOBAL DIRECTIVES ####

# Where to place auxiliary files[m
$WorkDirectory /var/lib/rsyslog

[34m# Use default timestamp format[m
$ActionFileDefaultTemplate RSYSLOG_TraditionalFileFormat

[34m# File syncing capability is disabled by default. This feature is usually not required,
# not useful and an extreme performance hit
#$ActionFileEnableSync on

# Include all config files in /etc/rsyslog.d/[m
$IncludeConfig /etc/rsyslog.d/*.conf

[34m# Turn off message reception via local log socket;
# local messages are retrieved through imjournal now.[m
$OmitLocalLogging on

[34m# File to store the position in the journal[m
$IMJournalStateFile imjournal.state

[?1049h[?1h=GREP(1)                               General Commands Manual                               GREP(1)[m
[m
[1mNAME[0m[m
       grep, egrep, fgrep - print lines matching a pattern[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTIONS[24m] [4mPATTERN[24m [[4mFILE[24m...][m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTIONS[24m] [[1m-e[0m [4mPATTERN[24m | [1m-f[0m [4mFILE[24m] [[4mFILE[24m...][m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       [1mgrep[0m searches the named input [4mFILE[24ms (or standard input if no files are named, or if a single[m
       hyphen-minus ([1m-[0m) is given as file name) for lines containing a match to the  given  [4mPATTERN[24m.[m
       By default, [1mgrep[0m prints the matching lines.[m
[m
       In  addition,  two  variant  programs  [1megrep[0m  and [1mfgrep[0m are available.  [1megrep[0m is the same as[m
       [1mgrep[0m [1m-E[0m.  [1mfgrep[0m is the same as [1mgrep[0m [1m-F[0m.  Direct invocation  as  either  [1megrep[0m  or  [1mfgrep[0m  is[m
       deprecated,  but  is  provided  to  allow  historical  applications that rely on them to run[m
       unmodified.[m
[m
[1mOPTIONS[0m[m
   [1mGeneric[0m [1mProgram[0m [1mInformation[0m[m
       [1m--help[0m Print a usage message briefly summarizing these command-line  options  and  the  bug-[m
              reporting address, then exit.[m
[7m Manual page grep(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)[27m[K[K/[Krr[Kee[Kcc[Kuu[Krr[Kss[Kvv[K[Kee[K[1;1HGREP(1)                               General Commands Manual                               GREP(1)[m
[2;1H[m
[3;1H[1mNAME[0m[m
[4;1H       grep, egrep, fgrep - print lines matching a pattern[m
[5;1H[m
[6;1H[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
[7;1H       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTIONS[24m] [4mPATTERN[24m [[4mFILE[24m...][m
[8;1H       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTIONS[24m] [[1m-e[0m [4mPATTERN[24m | [1m-f[0m [4mFILE[24m] [[4mFILE[24m...][m
[9;1H[m
[10;1H[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
[11;1H       [1mgrep[0m searches the named input [4mFILE[24ms (or standard input if no files are named, or if a single[m
[12;1H       hyphen-minus ([1m-[0m) is given as file name) for lines containing a match to the  given  [4mPATTERN[24m.[m

[4;1H       grep, egrep, fgrep - print lines matching a pattern[m

[7;1H       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTIONS[24m] [4mPATTERN[24m [[4mFILE[24m...][m
[8;1H       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTIONS[24m] [[1m-e[0m [4mPATTERN[24m | [1m-f[0m [4mFILE[24m] [[4mFILE[24m...][m
[9;1H[m
[10;1H[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
[11;1H       [1mgrep[0m searches the named input [4mFILE[24ms (or standard input if no files are named, or if a single[m
[12;1H       hyphen-minus ([1m-[0m) is given as file name) for lines containing a match to the  given  [4mPATTERN[24m.[m
[13;1H       By default, [1mgrep[0m prints the matching lines.[m
[14;1H[m
[15;1H       In  addition,  two  variant  programs  [1megrep[0m  and [1mfgrep[0m are available.  [1megrep[0m is the same as[m
[16;1H       [1mgrep[0m [1m-E[0m.  [1mfgrep[0m is the same as [1mgrep[0m [1m-F[0m.  Direct invocation  as  either  [1megrep[0m  or  [1mfgrep[0m  is[m
[17;1H       deprecated,  but  is  provided  to  allow  historical  applications that rely on them to run[m
[18;1H       unmodified.[m
[19;1H[m
[20;1H[1mOPTIONS[0m[m
[21;1H   [1mGeneric[0m [1mProgram[0m [1mInformation[0m[m
[22;1H       [1m--help[0m Print a usage message briefly summarizing these command-line  options  and  the  bug-[m
[23;1H              reporting address, then exit.[m
[24;1H...skipping...
              silently  skip  directories.   If  [4mACTION[24m  is  [1m[7mrecurse[27m[0m,  read  all  files  under each[m
              directory, recursively, following symbolic links only if  they  are  on  the  command[m
              line.  This is equivalent to the [1m-r[0m option.[m
[m
       [1m--exclude=[0m[4mGLOB[24m[m
              Skip  files whose base name matches [4mGLOB[24m (using wildcard matching).  A file-name glob[m
              can use [1m*[0m, [1m?[0m, and [1m[[0m...[1m][0m  as wildcards,  and  [1m\[0m  to  quote  a  wildcard  or  backslash[m
              character literally.[m
[m
       [1m--exclude-from=[0m[4mFILE[24m[m
              Skip  files  whose base name matches any of the file-name globs read from [4mFILE[24m (using[m
              wildcard matching as described under [1m--exclude[0m).[m
[m
       [1m--exclude-dir=[0m[4mDIR[24m[m
              Exclude directories matching the pattern [4mDIR[24m from recursive searches.[m
[m
       [1m-I[0m     Process a binary file as if it did not contain matching data; this is  equivalent  to[m
              the [1m--binary-files=without-match[0m option.[m
[m
       [1m--include=[0m[4mGLOB[24m[m
              Search  only files whose base name matches [4mGLOB[24m (using wildcard matching as described[m
              under [1m--exclude[0m).[m
